==Trivia==
*''{{Wp|Fidelio}}'' is an Opera by {{Wp|Ludwig van Beethoven}}. It is also famous for being the password from the ''{{Wp|Eyes Wide Shut}}'' movie by {{Wp|Stanley Kubrik}}, although in the novella ''{{Wp|Dream Story}}'' by {{Wp|Arthur Schnitzler}}, on which the movie is based, the password was apparently "Denmark". Etymologically the word appears to have latin roots (fidelis, fidele, fidelior), and basically means faithful.

